cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry (packing in Euclidean space) and analyzes its complexity using techniques from algorithms and graph theory. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The problem is also related to graph theory, as it involves finding an independent set in an intersection graph, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as likely sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new measure of fatness and analyzes its impact on the complexity, which could fall under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper mentions lower bounds based on the Exponential Time Hypothesis (ETH), which is a common tool in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
